# Python Standards

- Python 3.12+. Use built-in generics (`list[str]`, `dict[str, int]`, `X | None`).
- All DB operations must be `async`/`await` using SQLAlchemy async session.
- Use `Mapped` / `mapped_column` (SQLAlchemy 2.x declarative style) for all models.
- Type-hint every function signature. No bare `Any`.
- Keep routers thin — business logic belongs in a service layer, not inline in route handlers.
